t/Prelude.html#Subtype\">//</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">p₂</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">}</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Logic/Equiv/Defs.html#Equiv\">≃</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Quotient\">Quotient</a> <span class=\"fn\">s₂</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Subtype of the quotient is equivalent to the quotient of the subtype. Let `α` be a setoid with\nequivalence relation `~`. Let `p₂` be a predicate on the quotient type `α/~`, and `p₁` be the lift\nof this predicate to `α`: `p₁ a ↔ p₂ ⟦a⟧`. Let `~₂` be the restriction of `~` to `{x // p₁ x}`.\nThen `{x // p₂ x}` is equivalent to the quotient of `{x // p₁ x}` by `~₂`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Equiv/Basic.html#Equiv.subtypeQuotientEquivQuotientSubtype","kind":"def","line":579,"name":"Equiv.subtypeQuotientEquivQuotientSubtype","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/8f9d9cff6bd728b17a24e163c9402775d9e6a365/Mathlib/Logic/Equiv/Basic.lean#L579-L595"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Logic/Equiv/Basic.html#Equiv.Perm.extendDomain_trans\"><span class=\"name\">Equiv</span>.<span class=\"name\">Perm</span>.<span class=\"name\">extendDomain_trans</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α'</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_9}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">β'</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_10}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">p</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">β'</span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\